The former ITN presenter, 78, will instead host special programmes. His final edition of the Classic FM Concert with John Suchet is on Friday.  He said: "After a full-time career in TV news, it has been an utter joy for me to have a second career indulging my lifelong passion for classical music." Philip Noyce, the station's managing editor, said: "Ever since he joined Classic FM, he has shared our vision to make classical music accessible to all." 